Package: imputefinder
Title: Condition-Aware Missingness Classification for Proteomics
Version: 0.99.4
Authors@R:
    person("Emir", "Turkes", email = "emir.turkes@eturkes.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Classifies protein-intensity missingness independently within
    experimental conditions while preserving biologically plausible
    condition-specific on/off features. ImputeFinder distinguishes likely
    missing-not-at-random (MNAR) blocks from likely missing-at-random (MAR) or
    complete blocks using condition-specific intensity profiles, automatic or
    manual cutoffs, and strict-majority evidence. It accepts unnormalised log2
    quantitative-proteomics intensities in ordinary matrices or
    SummarizedExperiment objects and returns filtered, seed-modified data with
    auditable classifications, cutoff diagnostics, and seed provenance for
    downstream normalisation and imputation. An experimental input-first
    sidecar records typed design context, original missingness evidence, input
    identity, classic-fit compatibility, and explicit unavailable modules.
